### 2. Refactor Validator Class (packages/utils/src/validator/Validator.ts)

**Key Requirements:**
- Replace internal validation logic with Zod schemas
- Rename `Validator.new()` to `Validator.of()`
- Keep the external API identical: `{ isValid: boolean, error: string | null }`
- Maintain first-error behavior (stop at first validation failure)
- Preserve Mustache template support for error messages
- Keep all existing methods: `.alpha()`, `.length()`, `.uuid()`, `.url()`, `.datetime()`, `.in()`, `.gt()`, `.gte()`, `.lt()`, `.lte()`, `.empty()`, `.nil()`, `.notNil()`, `.string()`
- Add new methods:
  - `.regex(pattern: RegExp, error: string)`: validate against a regex pattern
  - `.refine(predicate: (value: TValue) => boolean, error: string)`: custom validation predicate
  - `.notEmpty(error: string)`: validate non-empty strings (trim + length > 0)

**Implementation Strategy:**
- Store a Zod schema internally (`z.any()` initially)
- Each validation method chains a new Zod refinement/check onto the schema
- The `.validate()` method calls `schema.safeParse(value)` and maps Zod errors to the first error string
- Use `z.string().regex()` for `.regex()`
- Use `z.any().refine()` for `.refine()`
- Use `z.string().min(1).refine((v) => v.trim().length > 0)` for `.notEmpty()`
- Keep static `combine()` method unchanged

**Example Refactored Structure:**
```typescript
import Mustache from 'mustache';
import { z, ZodSchema } from 'zod';

export class Validator<TValue> {
  private schema: ZodSchema;
  private _value: TValue;

  private constructor(value: TValue) {
    this.schema = z.any(); // Start with permissive schema
    this._value = value;
  }

  static of<TValue>(value: TValue): Validator<TValue> {
    return new Validator<TValue>(value);
  }

  // Keep existing .new() for backward compatibility during migration
  static new<TValue>(value: TValue): Validator<TValue> {
    return Validator.of(value);
  }

  public validate() {
    const result = this.schema.safeParse(this._value);
    if (result.success) {
      return { isValid: true, error: null };
    }
    // Extract first error message from Zod error
    const firstError = result.error.errors[0]?.message || 'Validation failed';
    return { isValid: false, error: firstError };
  }

  public regex(pattern: RegExp, error: string): Validator<TValue> {
    this.schema = this.schema.pipe(z.string().regex(pattern, { message: error }));
    return this;
  }

  public refine(predicate: (value: TValue) => boolean, error: string): Validator<TValue> {
    this.schema = this.schema.refine(predicate, { message: error });
    return this;
  }

  public notEmpty(error: string): Validator<TValue> {
    this.schema = this.schema.pipe(
      z.string().min(1, error).refine((v) => v.trim().length > 0, { message: error })
    );
    return this;
  }

  // Refactor existing methods to use Zod...
  public uuid(error: string): Validator<TValue> {
    this.schema = this.schema.pipe(z.string().uuid({ message: error }));
    return this;
  }

  public url(error: string): Validator<TValue> {
    this.schema = this.schema.pipe(z.string().url({ message: error }));
    return this;
  }

  // ... etc for all other methods
}
```

